<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - Meritor Transfer Cases MTC-4208, -4210, and -4213 - Power
        Take-Off (PTO) - Install PTO Onto Transfer Case
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Install PTO Onto Transfer Case</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two dowel pins into the transfer case PTO flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a thin coating of Loctite&#174; 518 gasket sealant to the entire PTO flange mounting
                surface (Figure 68).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the PTO assembly onto the output shaft spline. Align the assembly to the two dowel
                pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the washers and mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to 60-75 lb-ft (81-102 Nm).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the PTO air control line and fitting. Follow the vehicle manufacturer's
                instructions.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
